name: dnr-east-central-and-southeast-minnesota-fall-color-infrared-imagery-2011
notes: This dataset contains 4 Band (RGBI) digital orthophoto imagery in two regions of Minnesota: Aitkin, Anoka, Benton, Carlton, Chisago, Kanabec, Mille Lacs, Pine, Sherburne, and the northern portion of Washington counties in East-Central Minnesota, and Fillmore, Goodhue, Houston, Olmsted, Wabasha, and Winona counties in Southeast Minnesota. The orthophotos are 0.5-meter ground sample distance (GSD) and are in UTM Zone 15, NAD83 (meters). The tiling format of the imagery is based on a 3.75' x 3.75' quarter quadrangle with a 150 meter buffer on all four sides. This metadata record was created by MnGeo using information supplied by DNR and Surdex Corporation.
